The paper discusses a new approach to fuzzing, which is a technique used for software vulnerability detection. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also evaluates the proposed approach on real-world applications, which involves testing and security (cs.CR). The implementation of the approach involves integrating multiple fuzzing strategies, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of seed synchronization and result integration mechanisms, which are related to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses ensemble learning as inspiration for the proposed approach, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
